A number of prominent conservative activists have had their accounts suspended by Chase Bank in recent weeks.
Activist Laura Loomer, who has already been banned by PayPal, claims she had her account suspended by Chase Bank.
The idea that citizens could be cut off from using a bank because of their political views is extremely dangerous.
A world where your political views could keep you from being able to get credit or run a business.
Republicans in the Senate should demand that Chase executives come before them and answer some hard questions about targeting customers for their political views.